<paragraph id="8BC436C8FFFEFF8FFF7FFE82FE9BFDD4" blockId="7.[151,1437,259,538]" pageId="7" pageNumber="189">
<emphasis id="B90FEADAFFFEFF8FFF7FFE82FD25FEAB" bold="true" box="[199,746,331,358]" pageId="7" pageNumber="189">Additions and corrections to the description.</emphasis>
Detailed nymphal characters of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D4BFFFEFF8FFBDDFE85FA52FEA8" authorityName="Kubendran &amp; Balasubramanian" authorityYear="2015" box="[1125,1437,332,358]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Nigrobaetis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paramakalyani">
<emphasis id="B90FEADAFFFEFF8FFBDDFE85FA52FEA8" box="[1125,1437,332,358]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="189">Nigrobaetis paramakalyani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are mentioned in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEA4B39FFFEFF8FFEE4FEB9FDA1FE44" author="Kubendran, T. &amp; Balasubramanian, C. &amp; Selvakumar, C. &amp; Gattolliat, J. L. &amp; Sivaramakrishnan, K. G." box="[348,622,367,394]" pageId="7" pageNumber="189" pagination="188 - 200" refId="ref3726" refString="Kubendran, T., Balasubramanian, C., Selvakumar, C., Gattolliat, J. L. &amp; Sivaramakrishnan, K. G. (2015) Contribution to the knowledge of Tenuibaetis Kang &amp; Yang 1994, Nigrobaetis Novikova &amp; Kluge 1987 and Labiobaetis Novikova &amp; Kluge 1987 (Ephemeroptera: Baetidae) from the Western Ghats (India). Zootaxa, 3957 (2), 188 - 200. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3957.2.3" type="journal article" year="2015">
Kubendran 
<emphasis id="B90FEADAFFFEFF8FFE58FEB9FDDDFE44" box="[480,530,368,394]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="189">et al</emphasis>
. (2015)
</bibRefCitation>
. However, there are several errors in the description made. The addition and corrections to the description are listed as follows: i) posterior margin of tergum with long and apically blunt triangular spines on segments I to X (
<figureCitation id="13402A4DFFFEFF8FFDF5FE71FD66FE1C" box="[589,681,440,466]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1934,1958]" captionTargetBox="[190,1406,187,1884]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[180,1406,181,1910]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Nigrobaetis paramakalyani (photos by K.A. Subramanian). A) Male nymph; B) Tergal coloration; C) Posterotergal spines of segment IV; D) Paraproct; E) Gill IV" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5840745" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5840745/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="189">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
); ii) gill IV elongated with dark margin, relatively long setae and serrated all along margins, tracheation well visible but poorly divided (
<figureCitation id="13402A4DFFFEFF8FFC01FE15FBDEFE38" box="[953,1041,476,502]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1934,1958]" captionTargetBox="[190,1406,187,1884]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[180,1406,181,1910]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Nigrobaetis paramakalyani (photos by K.A. Subramanian). A) Male nymph; B) Tergal coloration; C) Posterotergal spines of segment IV; D) Paraproct; E) Gill IV" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5840745" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5840745/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="189">Fig. 4E</figureCitation>
); iii) paraproct with 9–10 marginal spines (
<figureCitation id="13402A4DFFFEFF8FFF55FDC9FE88FDD4" box="[237,327,512,538]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1934,1958]" captionTargetBox="[190,1406,187,1884]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[180,1406,181,1910]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Nigrobaetis paramakalyani (photos by K.A. Subramanian). A) Male nymph; B) Tergal coloration; C) Posterotergal spines of segment IV; D) Paraproct; E) Gill IV" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5840745" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5840745/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="189">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
